19/07/2007
BELGRADE, Serbia -- War crimes prosecutors indicted on Wednesday (July 18th) a former Kosovo Albanian guerrilla for atrocities against Serbian civilians during the Kosovo conflict.
Sinan Morina, who was a member of the Kosovo Liberation Army's "Orahovac Group", was one of 35 indicted for forced detention, torture and rape of Serbs, the killing of eight detainees, and destruction of Serb property and religious objects in the Orahovac village of Opterusa in July 1998.
Morina was arrested in Montenegro and extradited to Serbia in December.
(Tanjug, B92, FoNet, RTS - 18/07/07)
